"{\"uid\": \"mysailing.com.au-paris-olympics-day-8-wearn-maintains-mens-dinghy-lead\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Brin Liddell and Rhiannan Brown CREDIT Sailing Energy  Nia Jerwood and Conor Nicholas CREDIT Sailing Energy  Matt Wearn CREDIT Sailing Energy  Reigning Olympic champion Matt Wearn put together another solid day in a fading Mistral breeze today to hold his lead atop the Men's Dinghy leaderboard.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 4, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"score\": 0.9999532526421057, \"rank\": 4.674954310881596e-05, \"text\": \"Brin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\"}, {\"begin\": 5, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9999999998085514, \"rank\": 1.9032962005060796e-10, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\", \"score\": 0.9999999999345164, \"rank\": 6.543612172122106e-11, \"text\": \"Mistral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\"}, {\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dinghy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He avoided a mass black-flagging in the first race of the day that caught several of his closest competitors out.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When a black flag (BFD) is displayed by the Race Committee, if a competitor false starts, the penalty is the equivalent of the total fleet plus one, in this case 44 points.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7286212818472917e-16, \"text\": \"BFD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While his competitors toiled with the aftermath of accumulating a BFD, Matt went on to post two tenth place finishes and pressed home his advantage with two days of sailing to go in Marseille.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7286212818472917e-16, \"text\": \"BFD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KITS\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.999960903861691, \"rank\": 3.9097666731261525e-05, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cypriot Pavlos Kontides is now his closest competitor after steaming home for a seventh in the second race of the day in conditions that required the full set of skills from the fleet.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 779, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyprus\", \"score\": 0.999999962984021, \"rank\": 1.951827358290058e-08, \"text\": \"Cypriot\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyprus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cyprus\"}, {\"begin\": 787, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pavlos_Kontides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pavlos Kontides\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pavlos_Kontides\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pavlos_Kontides\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We did the first race in the dying Mistral and it was one of those races where you did not really know what was going to happen,\\\" said Wearn of the conditions.\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 1125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\", \"score\": 0.9999999999345164, \"rank\": 6.543612172122106e-11, \"text\": \"Mistral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsurfing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the second race the westerly had kicked in and we got a race in that, but you did not really know how far it was going to go or if it was going to come back so it made for some tricky racing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are two more qualifying races scheduled for tomorrow and the Medal Race set to take place on Tuesday 6 August.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The high-speed Kite Foiling class made their Olympic debut today, a discipline that sees foiling boards powered by kites that go three times the speed of the wind.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the medal prospects in the Women's division is Townsville Yacht Club athlete Breiana Whitehead, who has consistently placed near the top of the fleet over the past two years and took out the Overall winner at this year's Palma regatta.\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Townsville\", \"score\": 0.9999999994984137, \"rank\": 5.008625692478718e-10, \"text\": \"Townsville\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Townsville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Townsville\"}, {\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_North_Whitehead\", \"score\": 0.86217504823226, \"rank\": 0.15978079698797845, \"text\": \"Whitehead\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_North_Whitehead\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_North_Whitehead\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Breiana got a great start to her Olympic campaign showing a lot of confidence and speed on the water,\\\" noted Australian Olympic Sailing Team Leader Iain Brambell.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9900164593344707, \"rank\": 0.01007804774942276, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sailing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Sailing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sailing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sailing_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2001, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iain_Brambell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Iain Brambell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iain_Brambell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iain_Brambell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is really tight racing in the Kite event, and she currently sits just ten points off the podium.\\\"\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kite\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.515968491459463e-29, \"text\": \"Kite\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kite\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kite\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's Mixed Dinghy team of Nia Jerwood and Conor Nicholas posted a third and a sixteenth from their two races today to sit eighth overall.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998921499709608, \"rank\": 6.19785383685994e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 2152, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nia_Jerwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nia Jerwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nia_Jerwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nia_Jerwood\"}, {\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.997946668559291, \"rank\": 0.0020325765780771195, \"text\": \"Nicholas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's all to play for still,\\\" said Nicholas after racing.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.997946668559291, \"rank\": 0.0020325765780771195, \"text\": \"Nicholas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone's making mistakes and as you get less and less races to go, the pressure dials up and people start making even bigger mistakes.\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to keep a calm head and its game on.\\\"\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zoe Thomson fought valiantly in the Women's Dinghy, and she will take every opportunity to put her best foot forward in the final two qualifying races tomorrow.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2509, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"score\": 0.9999990085512221, \"rank\": 9.07756313311428e-07, \"text\": \"Zoe\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\"}, {\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Thomson\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.397765355263711e-11, \"text\": \"Thomson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Thomson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Thomson\"}, {\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dinghy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dinghy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The young Mixed Multihull team of Brin Liddell and Rhiannan Brown continue to knock on the door of the top ten as they sit in 12thoverall.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multihull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Multihull\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multihull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Multihull\"}, {\"begin\": 2705, \"end\": 2709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"score\": 0.9999532526421057, \"rank\": 4.674954310881596e-05, \"text\": \"Brin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\